Through lecturing and active group-works, discussions students will obtain knowledge on following topics: different definitions of organisation, parameters of organisation (objectives, mission, vision, structure, strategy, efficiency, and organisation culture); how related organisation culture and national culture are; organisational approaches through classical theories (Taylor, Fayol, Weber)till the nowadays post modernistic approaches; classifications of organisations; formulation of organisations and changes-drifts in the principles of organisations functioning .Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduce to the students different theoretical approaches of organisations and to provide basic knowledge for analysing organisations. Introductory course giving basic knowledge and preparation for following courses: organisation management and organisational behaviour.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student will have knowledge on different organisation definitions, theoretical organisational approaches. Student is able to identify and analyse different organisational parameters and has knowledge on nowadays trends in organisational thinking and changes.
